OK; I've just spent a couple of days playing this game, and I think I'm about ready to turn in my verdict.

Pros:

 - Interesting storyline;
 - Decent(ish) combat engine;
 - Some downright funny moments.

Cons:

 - Opaque combat mechanics (i.e., lack of walkthrough, ingame pedia or other assistance to help understand these numbers getting crunched);
 - Zurbaran is USELESS *sadface*;
 - The. Baroness. OMG, the Baroness....where to start. The bonus objective is only achieveable if you've looked up where the traps are placed - and that's just to start!
 - Siege of Morbal. Nothing ticks one off quite like pushing ahead, winning a tough battle....then, as you're winning, having a rock fall on two characters' heads at once, taking them entirely out of the fight arbitrarily!
 - No "RP" in "RPG" - it's a combat grinder, little more. There are hints of an interesting story, but no background, no dialogue, no choices....

Overall, Blackguards feels very, very old-school (think JRPG from the mid-90s, but darker and edgier) - 2014 was better than this! Would not recommend unless on significant discount...

